headline: If the Fed Keeps Cutting Interest Rates, This Stock Could Be a Winner
summary: UPS (NYSE: UPS) continues to struggle through a difficult period.  The small package delivery market is over capacity, pressuring pricing power at a time when a weak economy is encouraging customers to shift to cheaper delivery options.  It all adds up to a difficult period for UPS, and the company will end 2024 with significantly lower earnings than management anticipated at the start of the year.
